    "attributes": {
        "action": "Take action to pressure Russia and support refugees over anti-LGBTQ+ measures",
        "additional_details": "We want the Government to take action to pressure Russia and support refugees over anti-LGBTQ+ measures.\r\n \r\nWe want the UK Government to:\r\n \r\n- Offer automatic asylum and refugee status for any person escaping anti-LGBTQ+ measures in Russia\r\n- Use its global influence to pressure the Russian government to abandon anti-LGBTQ+ measures\r\n- Urge the United Nations and human rights organisations to intervene\r\n- Impose sanctions on Russia until anti-LGBTQ+ measures are abandoned\r\n \r\nAn attack on human rights and the LGBTQ+ community anywhere is an attack on people everywhere.\r\n",
        "background": "Russia\u2019s supreme court ruled the \u2018international LGBT movement\u2019 as \u2018extremist' in November 2023. We are concerned this is leading to the increased persecution of people suspected to be LGBTQ+.",
